 Definately does not go for DS. the person being PL'd just hasta do more direct damage to the mob(melee or spells) than anyone else to get exp. I use a druid or cleric(mark of retribution) fairly often to PL. And pulling 3-4 mobs at a time to the lowbie and letting them all beat on him works great as long as he hits every one at least once.<br>
<br>
 Actually with a wiz and the flux staff to hold agro it might work to DS yourself and let that do damage to the mob while the lobie attacks from behind. So long as they hit the mob once they *should* get the exp. DS dmg is considered environmental or some such and not attributed to any specific player. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=372117"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spingrim3c.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jentrikenaspenbark>Jentriken Aspenbark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 271<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/20/03 6:08:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25469.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> no</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>if the PLer uses a DoT and the DoT did more damage than the PLed, the PLed will not get xp, whether the PLer is in zone or not. IIRC, the same goes for DS.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
